@startuml
title Patrón Modelo-Vista-Plantilla (MVC adaptado por Django)

node "Navegador Web" as Browser

package "Django Framework" {
  component "urls.py (Controlador de Rutas)" as Router
  component "views.py (Vista/Controlador Lógico)" as View
  component "models.py (Modelo)" as Model
  component "templates/*.html (Plantilla/Vista UI)" as Template
}

database "Base de Datos (SQLite)" as DB

Browser -> Router : 1. Petición HTTP (GET/POST)
Router -> View : 2. Enruta a la función correspondiente
View -> Model : 3. Solicita/Actualiza datos
Model <-> DB : 4. Consulta ORM (SQL)
Model --> View : 5. Retorna QuerySet/Objetos
View -> Template : 6. Pasa contexto (datos)
Template --> View : 7. Retorna HTML renderizado
View --> Browser : 8. Respuesta HTTP (HTML/JSON)

note bottom of View
  **Patrón MVC (Model-View-Controller)**
  En Django se conoce como MTV (Model-Template-View).
  - Model = Models
  - View = Templates
  - Controller = Views + URLs
end note
@enduml
